[The analysis of the disease situation in the Samokov region of Bulgaria is
consistent with an outbreak of norovirus infection, although the laboratory
analysis is incomplete. Particularly unusual is the extent of the outbreak
and the failure, so far, to identify the actual source of what is regarded
as a point source epidemic.
A map of Bulgaria showing the location of the city of Samokov, south of the
capital Sofia, is available at
